The paper discusses a control system for mobile robots that deals with uncertainty in navigating and exploring unknown environments. This topic is closely related to robotics (cs.RO), as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques used to make decisions based on sensor data. Computer vision (cs.CV) is also relevant for processing visual information, and systems engineering (cs.SY) may be applicable for designing and implementing the control system.
